<paragraph id="8B98369F770C7F2081AFA5BCFE61FC7E" blockId="35.[151,1055,823,923]" box="[151,510,896,923]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F2081AFA5BCFF6CFC7E" box="[151,243,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="97.[151,250,1713,1737]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,190,1679]" captionTargetId="figure-19@97.[169,1418,181,1689]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal view of males of: a) Belonuchus magnistylus (paratype), b) B. metafemoralis (paratype), c) B. oxyporimimus (paratype), d) B. pulcher (paratype), e) B. oxyporinus (holotype, NHM©), f) B. oxyporinus, g) B. rufisternus (holotype), h) B. singularis (holotype). Scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630887/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs. 3b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F2081C7A5BCFEACFC7E" box="[255,307,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="106.[151,250,1870,1894]" captionTargetBox="[191,1398,191,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-25@106.[165,1422,181,1846]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 12. Mesoventrite of males of: a) Belonuchus viridipennis, b) Belonuchus sp. Q, c) B. cyanipennis. Ventral view of the left femur of male anterior leg of: d) B. apiciventris, e) B. oxyporimimus, f) B. oxyporinus, g) B. tepoztecus, h) B. bidens, i) B. viridipennis. Ventral view of the left posterior leg of males of: j) B. julietitae, k) B. linuzensis (small specimen), l) B. linuzensis (large specimen), m) B. metafemoralis, n) B. oxyporimimus, o) B. oxyporinus. Red arrow: intercoxal process of the mesoventrite, blue arrow: transverse discal ridge." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630915/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770C7F2081C7A5BCFEACFC7E" box="[255,307,896,922]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="m" value="12.0">12m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F208007A5BCFEFAFC7F" box="[319,357,896,923]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="109.[151,250,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[175,1417,182,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-19@109.[160,1427,181,1797]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURE 15. Male pregenital sternite of: a) Belonuchus alternans, b) B. oxyporinus, c) B. tepoztecus, d) B. jalappensis, e) B. iridescens, f) B. platypterus, g) B. cyanipennis, h) B. apiciventris, i) B. linuzensis, j) B. metafemoralis, k) B. rufisternus, l) B. tenuistylus, m) B. bidens, n) B. pollens, o) B. longitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630921/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">15j</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F208049A5BCFE09FC7E" box="[369,406,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="112.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[174,1411,182,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-25@112.[173,1413,181,1775]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURE 18. Male genital sternite of: a) Belonuchus altenans, b) B. apiciventris, c) B. cariniventris, d) B. colon, e) B. confusus, f) B. julietitae, g) B. magnistylus, h) B. linuzensis, i) B. metafemoralis, j) B. oxyporimimus, k) B. oxyporinus, l) B. pulcher, m) B. rufisternus, n) B. singularis, o) B. tenuistylus. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630925" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630925/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">18i</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F20809BA5BCFE56FC7E" box="[419,457,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="115.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[160,1425,189,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-19@115.[151,1436,181,1832]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURE 21. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus alternans, b) B. apiciventris, c) B. cariniventris, d) B. colon, e) B. confusus, f) B. julietitae, g) B. linuzensis, h) B. magnistylus, i) B. metafemoralis. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630931/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">21i</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F2080EDA5BCFE61FC7E" box="[469,510,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="121.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,184,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-19@121.[214,1374,174,1912]" captionTargetPageId="121" captionText="FIGURE 27. Geographical distribution in Mexico of: a) Belonuchus erichsoni and B. oxyporinus; b) B. longitarsus, B. metafemoralis, B. mixtecus, B. optatus and B. rufiventris." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630947/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">27b</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770C7F2081AFA5F4FCD4FBAA" blockId="35.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Total body length 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770C7F208050A5F4FE50FC07" box="[360,463,968,995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="11.4">11.4 mm</quantity>
. Black on head, antennae, pronotum, posterior 3/4 of fifth visible abdominal segment and all sixth, prosternum, anterior half of mesoventrite and abdominal styli. Reddish on elytra, legs, posterior half of mesoventrite, metaventrite, first four visible abdominal segments and anterior 1/4 of fifth visible segment. Mandibles, maxillary and labial palpi, and genital segment brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770C7F2081FFA264FAA2FA8A" blockId="35.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770C7F2081FFA264FE98FB96" bold="true" box="[199,263,1112,1138]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Head</emphasis>
: transverse, slightly convex at posterior corners and on vertex; ratio length/width 0.74. Dorsal surface with indistinctly visible microsculpture of waved lines; sulcate longitudinal midline visible in anterior half of head; front with a narrow area clearly foveate near anterior margin. Eyes nearly 0.5 times the cephalic lateral length, not protruding at sides. Antennomere 4 slightly elongate, 5 almost as long as wide, 6–10 transverse. Mandibles 1.41 times longer than head; with two well separated teeth, basal tooth longer than middle tooth; mandibular channel with external margin widely separated from internal margin at base, internal margin carinate, extending forward slightly beyond level of middle tooth. Apical palpomere of maxillary and labial palpi nearly 1.25 times longer than preapical palpomere. Head 1.25 times wider than pronotum. Neck with wrinkled microsculpture ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770C7F2081FFA344FBAAF91E" blockId="35.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770C7F2081FFA344FEBFFA76" bold="true" box="[199,288,1400,1426]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Thorax</emphasis>
: each dorsal row of pronotum with four punctures; pronotum slightly longer than wide (ratio 1.13), almost as wide at anterior corners as at posterior corners (ratio 1.03). Scutellum and elytra with fine, sparse punctures and setae. Prosternum with area close to anterior margin slightly elevated, with microsculpture as on neck. Anterior half of mesoventrite with microsculpture as on neck; intercoxal process shield-shaped, lateral margin well developed; transverse discal ridge broadly U-shaped, laterally meeting with lateral margin of intercoxal process. Profemur with external row of spines initiating in basal fourth and reaching apex, but interrupted before apex, as if one or two spines were missing; spines increasing in size toward apex; internal margin developed only near apex, where bearing few spines. Metatrochanter modified like a hook, wide in basal 2/3 and slender and straight in distal third, ending in an angle of 90°, hook as long as 1/3 of length of metafemur (
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F2082C6A0A4FBF7F956" box="[1022,1128,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="106.[151,250,1870,1894]" captionTargetBox="[191,1398,191,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-25@106.[165,1422,181,1846]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 12. Mesoventrite of males of: a) Belonuchus viridipennis, b) Belonuchus sp. Q, c) B. cyanipennis. Ventral view of the left femur of male anterior leg of: d) B. apiciventris, e) B. oxyporimimus, f) B. oxyporinus, g) B. tepoztecus, h) B. bidens, i) B. viridipennis. Ventral view of the left posterior leg of males of: j) B. julietitae, k) B. linuzensis (small specimen), l) B. linuzensis (large specimen), m) B. metafemoralis, n) B. oxyporimimus, o) B. oxyporinus. Red arrow: intercoxal process of the mesoventrite, blue arrow: transverse discal ridge." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630915/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770C7F20850AA0A4FBF7F956" box="[1074,1128,1688,1714]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="m" value="12.0">12m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); metafemur with a convex carina near base of its ventral surface, delimiting a slight to moderate cavity to accommodate the hook. Metatibia weakly curved at internal margin near apex. Tarsomeres slightly flattened dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770C7F2081FFA138FDBEF812" blockId="35.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770C7F2081FFA138FEA3F8FA" bold="true" box="[199,316,1796,1822]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Abdomen</emphasis>
: first three visible tergites with posterior basal transverse carina well developed, adjacent area slightly depressed, narrow and with sparse wide-superficial punctures; remaining surface of tergites 1–3 and remaining tergites with fine, sparse punctures and setae. Anterior half of visible sternites 1–4 with wide-superficial punctures denser than on tergites 1–3, remaining surface only with fine, sparse punctures and setae. Male pregenital sternite with slight, broadly arcuate emargination (
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F208356A1A8FD57F84B" box="[622,712,1940,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="109.[151,250,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[175,1417,182,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-19@109.[160,1427,181,1797]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURE 15. Male pregenital sternite of: a) Belonuchus alternans, b) B. oxyporinus, c) B. tepoztecus, d) B. jalappensis, e) B. iridescens, f) B. platypterus, g) B. cyanipennis, h) B. apiciventris, i) B. linuzensis, j) B. metafemoralis, k) B. rufisternus, l) B. tenuistylus, m) B. bidens, n) B. pollens, o) B. longitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630921/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 15j</figureCitation>
). Male genital sternite short (2.0 times longer than wide), slightly asymmetrical, anterior portion occupying 30% and posterior portion 70% of its length, apical emargination deep (
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770C7F208198A1E0FF64F813" box="[160,251,2012,2039]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="112.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[174,1411,182,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-25@112.[173,1413,181,1775]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURE 18. Male genital sternite of: a) Belonuchus altenans, b) B. apiciventris, c) B. cariniventris, d) B. colon, e) B. confusus, f) B. julietitae, g) B. magnistylus, h) B. linuzensis, i) B. metafemoralis, j) B. oxyporimimus, k) B. oxyporinus, l) B. pulcher, m) B. rufisternus, n) B. singularis, o) B. tenuistylus. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630925" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630925/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 18i</figureCitation>
). Abdominal styli slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770B7F2781FFA6AAFF54FF1E" blockId="36.[151,1437,150,1293]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770B7F2781FFA6AAFEA5FF54" bold="true" box="[199,314,150,176]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Aedeagus</emphasis>
: length 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770B7F2780AFA6ABFE6EFF55" box="[407,497,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
; elongate shape, with a constriction in apical third; apex slightly rounded in ventral view and slightly acute in lateral view; in lateral view, basal half wider than apical half; internal sac visible (
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A770B7F278457A687FF21FF1E" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="115.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[160,1425,189,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-19@115.[151,1436,181,1832]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURE 21. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus alternans, b) B. apiciventris, c) B. cariniventris, d) B. colon, e) B. confusus, f) B. julietitae, g) B. linuzensis, h) B. magnistylus, i) B. metafemoralis. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630931/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 21i</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770B7F2781FFA73EFD50FD85" blockId="36.[151,1437,150,1293]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770B7F2781FFA73EFED8FEF8" bold="true" box="[199,327,258,284]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Variability</emphasis>
. Measurements and ratios (males n=3, females n=3): total body length in males 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770B7F2785DEA73FFAD3FEF9" box="[1254,1356,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.09" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="10.9">10.9 mm</quantity>
(range 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770B7F2781AFA71AFEA2FEA5" box="[151,317,294,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.15" metricValueMin="1.05" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="11.5" valueMin="10.5">10.5–11.5 mm</quantity>
), in females 10.7 (range 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A770B7F278368A71BFD69FEA5" box="[592,758,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" metricValueMax="1.13" metricValueMin="1.03" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="10.8" valueMax="11.3" valueMin="10.3">10.3–11.3 mm</quantity>
); ratio length/width of head in males 0.78 (range 0.76–0.80), in females 0.91 (range 0.90–0.93); ratio mandibular length/cephalic length in males 1.23 (range 1.04–1.37), in females 0.89 (range 0.81–1.00); ratio cephalic width/pronotal width in males 1.15 (range 1.13–1.19), in females 1.04 (range 1.02–1.06); ratio length/width of pronotum in males 1.11 (range 1.10–1.13) in females 1.14 (range 1.10–1.18); ratio anterior width/posterior with of pronotum in males 1.01 (range 1.00–1.03), in females 1.0 (without variation). In addition, there is a variation in the sulcate longitudinal midline of the head that can go further back than the eye level; dorsal rows of punctures in the pronotum are predominantly 5:5, but 6:6 and 4:5 also occur; in a female and a male the wide-superficial punctures of the abdomen appear denser; in 
<specimenCount id="9D21FD16770B7F278572A41FFB59FDD9" box="[1098,1222,547,573]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
the elytra and legs are reddish-dark, and the abdomen is shiny brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F770B7F2781FFA456FA83FCF1" blockId="36.[151,1437,150,1293]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770B7F2781FFA456FE53FD61" bold="true" box="[199,460,618,645]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Taxonomic comments</emphasis>
. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C770B7F27820EA457FC51FD61" authorityName="Márquez &amp; Asiain" authorityYear="2022" box="[822,974,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuistylus">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770B7F27820EA457FC51FD61" box="[822,974,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">B. tenuistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the fifth visible abdominal segment black in basal 3/4 and reddish in anterior 1/4, the metafemur of males has a cavity delimited by a carina where each hook is possibly accommodated, and in the particular shape of aedeagus and genital sternite; while 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C770B7F2781E5A4EBFEEAFD15" authorityName="Márquez &amp; Asiain" authorityYear="2022" box="[221,373,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuistylus">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770B7F2781E5A4EBFEEAFD15" box="[221,373,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">B. tenuistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the basal half of the fifth visible abdominal segment black and the apical half reddish, the metafemur of males lacks the cavity and carina, and they have a different aedeagus and genital sternite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D6514770B7F2781FFA523FC10FCB9" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B98369F770B7F2781FFA523FC10FCB9" blockId="36.[151,1437,150,1293]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D770B7F2781FFA523FED7FCDD" bold="true" box="[199,328,799,825]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of this species refers to the femur of the male posterior legs, with a cavity delimited by a carina, a structure that has not been observed in any other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
